On January 20, the first San Francisco JAM (Jenkins Area Meetup) of the new year was held at Mesosphereâ€™s offices. We had two speakers - myself, and Roger Ignazio, an infrastructure automation engineer at Mesosphere. Around forty people attended and enjoyed the food and drinks Mesosphere provided for us.

Links to the talks are below:

  • Elastic Jenkins with Mesos and DCOS, by Roger Ignazio

  • Who is Jenkins?, by Andrew Bayer

More JAMs will be happening in the coming months - for example, the first Los Angeles JAM is tentatively planned for early March, 2016! You can always find out the latest on JAMs around the world at the Jenkins Area Meetup page.
